<emphasis bold="true" box="[676,710,785,804]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">3–5</emphasis>
) and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schaum" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[762,1014,785,804]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopygothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atropurpurea">
<emphasis box="[762,1014,785,804]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Hoplopygothrix atropurpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1029,1063,785,804]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">6–8</emphasis>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1082,1126,785,804]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">3, 6)</emphasis>
Lateral view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[226,271,809,828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">4, 7)</emphasis>
Dorsal view; 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[394,438,809,828]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">5, 8)</emphasis>
Ventral view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="2.[173,660,887,1016]" lastBlockId="2.[707,1193,888,1201]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
the clypeus (absent in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ratcliffe" authorityYear="2011" box="[390,521,887,909]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopygothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boliviensis">
<emphasis box="[390,521,887,909]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">H. boliviensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, present in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schaum" baseAuthorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopygothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atropurpurea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">H. atropurpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), absence of a distinctly tawny tuft of setae at the apex of the scutellum (present in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schaum" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[173,340,967,989]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopygothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atropurpurea">
<emphasis box="[173,340,967,989]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">H. atropurpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), convex pygidium (flat in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schaum" baseAuthorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopygothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atropurpurea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">H. atropurpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), presence of cream-colored vittae or spots on the dorsum and venter (venter only in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schaum" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[707,865,914,936]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopygothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atropurpurea">
<emphasis box="[707,865,914,936]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">H. atropurpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and form of the male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[714,806,940,962]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="2.[197,237,785,804]" captionTargetBox="[173,1195,183,762]" captionTargetId="figure-243@2.[173,1195,183,762]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs. 3–8. Parameres of Hoplopygothrix boliviensis (3–5) and Hoplopygothrix atropurpurea (6–8). 3, 6) Lateral view; 4, 7) Dorsal view; 5, 8) Ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4893071" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4893071/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Figs. 3–8</figureCitation>
). The genitalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ratcliffe" authorityYear="2011" box="[989,1121,940,962]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopygothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boliviensis">
<emphasis box="[989,1121,940,962]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">H. boliviensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a proportionally longer basal piece, the parameres are not noticeably constricted laterally as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schaum" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[707,866,1020,1042]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopygothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atropurpurea">
<emphasis box="[707,866,1020,1042]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">H. atropurpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the apex lacks the distinctive spine seen in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schaum" baseAuthorityYear="1841" box="[900,1062,1047,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopygothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atropurpurea">
<emphasis box="[900,1062,1047,1069]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">H. atropurpurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ratcliffe" authorityYear="2011" box="[736,870,1073,1095]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Hoplopygothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="boliviensis">
<emphasis box="[736,870,1073,1095]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">H. boliviensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remains unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="65" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[707,1193,888,1201]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,812,1100,1121]" pageId="2" pageNumber="65">Biology.</emphasis>
A single specimen is insufficient to determine the extent of the geographic or temporal distributions. As with many captures of singletons, nothing is known of the biology of this species.
</paragraph>
